… Mark to chair convention  The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) 96th National Executive Committee (NEC) has finally thrown open the contest for the party’s 2023 presidential ticket. PDP’s position was made known during the party’s NEC meeting which held on Wednesday, in Abuja. Also, ahead of the party’s National Convention to elect the party’s presidential candidate, the party’s NEC also appointed former Senate President, David Mark, as chairman of the Convention Committee.
The party’s National Working Committee had set up a Zoning Committee headed by Benue State Governor, Samuel Ortom to examine the issue. The Committee submitted its report about a month ago.
